translated: Keiller, Harry Anker, director, Särö, born on May 20th in Särö, Halland. Son of engineer Harry Alexander K. and Kate Anker. Married to Kerstin Mark. Children: Ann, born in 1939, Eva, born in 1944. Completed Realexamen at the age of 26, studied at Gbgs hand :inst. in 1928. Worked in various positions in neighboring countries, as well as in Germany, England, USA and Canada. Employed at Stora Kopparbergs Bergsl. A-B in Falun in 1927, A-B August Leffler & Son in Gothenburg from 1929-1930, August Bolten in Hamburg in 1930, T. Phelan & Co. Ltd in Liverpool in 1931, A-B Sv. Amer. Linien from 1932 onwards, A-B Göta Kanal in Gothenburg in 1932, The Decca Scand. Agency in Gothenburg in the same year, director of A. Keiller & Co. A-B in Gothenburg since 1932, head of Bolinders Fabr. A-B office in Gothenburg since 1938, director of Harry Keillers A-B since 1945, and owner of Särö Värdshus. Chairman of Särö sailing club, member of the board of The Royal Bachelors Club, Halland tourist traffic association, Särö friends, Särö boat club, Särö road association, The British Factory in Gothenburg, among others. Lieutenant in the Swedish Volunteer Corps. Hobbies include sailing and tennis.
